definitions.definition: A government where power is shared by four people , especially ( historical ) the Herodian tetrarchy established in Judea after the death of Herod and the Tetrarchy of Diocletian which ruled the Roman Empire in the years 293-313.
The land ruled by such a government , either together or separately .
